I"J<p>Just out of boredom today, I decided to make a sort of CSS reset for
myself. Technically it’s more base styles than a reset seeing as it
has a lot of styling rather than just removing margins and padding.</p>

<p>I haven’t really tested it (OK, so not at all tested it), but I thought
other people may like it. Here it is in it’s uncompressed glory:</p>

<p><strong>EDIT:</strong> I have tested it in Webkit and Gecko (chrome and firefox) and
it works beautifully. I have also made a preview page. You can check it out
<a href="/reset_test.html"><strong>here</strong></a>.</p>

<figure class="highlight"><pre><code class="language-css" data-lang="css"><span class="c">/*
 * Tom Brunoli's CSS Base Styles
 * Updated 2011-05-12
 * 
 * Licenced under Creative Commons Attribution-ShareAlike
 * http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/3.0/
 *
 */</span>

<span class="c">/* Basics */</span>
<span class="nt">html</span><span class="o">,</span> <span class="nt">body</span>                      <span class="p">{</span> <span class="nl">margin</span><span class="p">:</span> <span class="m">0</span><span class="p">;</span> <span class="nl">padding</span><span class="p">:</span> <span class="m">0</span><span class="p">;</span> <span class="nl">background</span><span class="p">:</span> <span class="m">#efefef</span><span class="p">;</span> <span class="nl">color</span><span class="p">:</span> <span class="m">#444</span><span class="p">;</span> <span class="p">}</span>
